Clear and sunny- calm- air temp is 68 degrees.  Water color is slight tan.
Sunny- light haze- slight ripple- air temp 65- water light tan
Sunny- slight ripple on water- much rain recently
Sunny- slight chop on the water- water color seems more brown than usual.
Sunny- 70 degrees- air temp- slight chop on water- ice off 4-9-94.  Red-breasted mergansers feeding on the lake.
Sunny- slight ripple- air temp. 75 degrees.  Saw a pair of black terns circling lake-nesting pair   used to have 5-6 pair nesting on hummocks of floating lily ad roots about 20-25 years ago.
Very slight breeze- 90 degrees and sunny
Sunny- but very hazy due to Canadian forest fires- slight ripple
Sunny- slight chop- 75 degrees air temperature
Sunny- brisk breeze- moderate chop.  Water level: Summer Low

Large areas of good bass and bluegill spawning and fishing areas on this lake have been ruined by a DNR weed cutting project.  The cutting machine has uprooted large lily pad root hammocks which have drifted across the lake and are now roo
Lake is still suffering effects of UW/Department of Natural Resources weed removal experiment- there are still large masses of muck and lily pad roots.
I have a new/ replacement surface on my Secchi disk this year.  That may have helped me to get that exceptional 15.75 foot reading last month.
D.O sampled at 20 and 25 feet less than 1 ppm
